1
00:00:48,181 --> 00:00:49,739
...Kamchatka.

2
00:00:52,452 --> 00:00:55,853
<i>In the beginning there was
a cell, nothing else.</i>

3
00:00:55,989 --> 00:01:00,619
<i>That cell split into two, those
two into others, and so on.</i>

4
00:01:00,760 --> 00:01:04,787
<i>Some cells became plants,
others bugs...</i>

5
00:01:04,931 --> 00:01:06,558
<i>...others animals...</i>

6
00:01:06,699 --> 00:01:08,724
<i>...and others us.</i>

7
00:01:08,935 --> 00:01:12,666
<i>What they never explain
is what happens next...</i>

8
00:01:12,806 --> 00:01:16,674
<i>...between the moment
the cells become a person...</i>

9
00:01:16,810 --> 00:01:19,802
<i>...and that person
climbs the Himalayas...</i>

10
00:01:19,946 --> 00:01:21,573
<i>...discovers a vaccine...</i>

11
00:01:21,714 --> 00:01:24,945
<i>...or becomes a famous
escapist like Houdini.</i>

12
00:01:25,085 --> 00:01:26,746
<i>That is a real mystery.</i>

13
00:01:26,886 --> 00:01:30,253
<i>No textbook mentions this.
No teacher does.</i>

14
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:33,086
<i>But my dad did so.
Once.</i>

15
00:01:33,226 --> 00:01:35,023
<i>The last time I saw him.</i>

16
00:01:35,161 --> 00:01:38,528
<i>My story, like all stories,
begins with a cell...</i>

17
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:42,066
<i>...but ends in Kamchatka.</i>

18
00:01:45,472 --> 00:01:48,498
<i>Life,
the supreme mystery.</i>

19
00:01:48,641 --> 00:01:52,008
<i>The energy which induces
cells to join together...</i>

20
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:55,205
<i>Fall, 1976.
... and form tissues...</i>

21
00:01:55,348 --> 00:01:59,341
Days after
Argentina's military coup

22
00:02:03,456 --> 00:02:05,287
"o".

23
00:02:06,126 --> 00:02:08,924
It's got to have a vowel!

24
00:02:09,963 --> 00:02:12,454
Look at all the "a's"!

25
00:02:13,133 --> 00:02:14,293
"F"?

26
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,495
"T"?

27
00:02:23,009 --> 00:02:24,271
Mum!

28
00:02:32,085 --> 00:02:34,815
Ok, go.
I'll be outside.

29
00:02:38,458 --> 00:02:40,858
- When are you coming?
- After English.

30
00:02:40,994 --> 00:02:44,486
- My mum's making escalopes.
- Yes!

31
00:02:52,105 --> 00:02:54,630
ABRACADABRA

32
00:03:20,333 --> 00:03:23,632
Bertuccio's mum's
making escalopes.

33
00:03:24,204 --> 00:03:26,832
- You're an invader!
- Here.

34
00:03:27,407 --> 00:03:29,932
Wow!
The latest edition!

35
00:03:30,176 --> 00:03:32,167
Yes, just out.

36
00:03:38,585 --> 00:03:41,611
- Where are we going?
- To a friend's house.

37
00:03:41,754 --> 00:03:44,723
You took me out of
school just for that?

38
00:03:45,892 --> 00:03:47,917
We'll be back soon,
okay?

39
00:03:48,061 --> 00:03:49,653
It's Thursday, remember.

40
00:03:49,796 --> 00:03:52,856
I've got English, then
I'm going to Bertuccio's.

41
00:03:52,999 --> 00:03:54,694
- Not today.
- Why not?

42
00:03:54,834 --> 00:03:57,302
- We can't.
- Why not?

43
00:03:57,470 --> 00:04:00,633
- Because we're going on a trip.
- Aren't we going...

44
00:04:00,773 --> 00:04:05,369
...to your friends'? - We'll
drop in and set off from there.

45
00:04:09,315 --> 00:04:11,715
I don't want to go there.

46
00:04:11,851 --> 00:04:14,979
What am I gonna do?
I'll get bored.

47
00:04:20,493 --> 00:04:25,055
- So leave me here and pick me
up later from Bertuccio's. - No.

48
00:04:25,198 --> 00:04:27,666
I told you to leave me here
and pick me up later!

49
00:04:27,800 --> 00:04:30,769
- Are you crazy or what?
- Leave me here!

50
00:04:30,903 --> 00:04:33,098
- I won't!
- Why not?

51
00:04:33,239 --> 00:04:36,868
- Because I say so!
- Keep going, madam.

52
00:04:44,984 --> 00:04:47,919
It's not fair!
It's not fair!

53
00:04:55,695 --> 00:04:57,754
<i>The invaders...</i>

54
00:04:57,964 --> 00:05:01,058
<i>Aliens coming
from a dying planet.</i>

55
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:03,668
<i>Destination. ' The Earth.</i>

56
00:05:03,803 --> 00:05:07,034
<i>Purpose. '
To dominate the world.</i>

57
00:05:09,242 --> 00:05:11,802
<i>David Vincent has seen them.</i>

58
00:05:12,111 --> 00:05:16,138
<i>For him it all started one night
on a lonely country road...</i>

59
00:05:16,282 --> 00:05:18,147
Let me watch, you, Shorty!

60
00:05:18,284 --> 00:05:22,345
<i>...looking for a short-cut
he never found.</i>

61
00:05:22,588 --> 00:05:26,149
<i>It began with a closed
deserted diner...</i>

62
00:05:26,292 --> 00:05:30,422
<i>...and a man too exhausted
to continue his journey.</i>

63
00:05:31,030 --> 00:05:34,329
<i>A spaceship from another
galaxy landed...</i>

64
00:05:34,467 --> 00:05:36,230
I was in the laboratory...

65
00:05:36,369 --> 00:05:40,032
...when I saw her waving at me,
'Your husband on the phone! '

66
00:05:40,173 --> 00:05:43,472
I asked him what happened 'I'd
been trying to reach you at the...

67
00:05:43,609 --> 00:05:46,544
...law office and nobody
would answer! ' He told me...

68
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:50,410
...some militars had searched the
office and kidnapped Roberto...

69
00:05:50,550 --> 00:05:51,983
...his partner.

70
00:05:53,619 --> 00:05:56,918
What's wrong, sweetie?
Do you want something?

71
00:05:59,125 --> 00:06:03,186
- Where's the bathroom?
- Down the hall.

72
00:06:03,329 --> 00:06:06,355
- Do you want me to go
with you? - No.

73
00:06:23,583 --> 00:06:25,608
I'd rather sleep
on the floor.

74
00:06:25,752 --> 00:06:28,846
Little guy's kicking
the hell out of me.

75
00:06:30,957 --> 00:06:33,482
This bed is going to hell!

76
00:06:34,694 --> 00:06:37,458
Are you sleeping
there with mum?

77
00:06:43,069 --> 00:06:45,765
So, tell me.
What happened today?

78
00:06:45,905 --> 00:06:49,534
A girl saw the invaders
disintegrate a truck.

79
00:06:49,675 --> 00:06:52,974
Then David Vincent
had to find the driver...

80
00:06:53,112 --> 00:06:56,047
I saw that one,
about three times.

81
00:06:56,716 --> 00:06:59,310
Your mum?
How was she?

82
00:06:59,719 --> 00:07:01,550
The Rock!

83
00:07:02,388 --> 00:07:05,186
She didn't let me go
to Bertuccio's.

84
00:07:05,391 --> 00:07:08,758
- What happened to Roberto?
- What do you mean?

85
00:07:08,895 --> 00:07:11,090
Don't goof around.

86
00:07:13,099 --> 00:07:16,626
- Did mum tell you?
- They took him away, right?

87
00:07:16,869 --> 00:07:19,497
But nothing'll
happen to him?

88
00:07:19,639 --> 00:07:23,336
You'll get him out.
That's what lawyers are for.

89
00:07:25,545 --> 00:07:28,639
But Roberto's a lawyer, too.

90
00:07:30,149 --> 00:07:33,516
Do lawyers
get taken away, too?

91
00:07:35,822 --> 00:07:39,019
- Nothing will happen to you,
right? - No.

92
00:07:39,859 --> 00:07:41,884
Nothing.

93
00:07:42,361 --> 00:07:44,352
You know what
we're gonna do?

94
00:07:44,497 --> 00:07:47,091
Go away for a while,
till things calm down.

95
00:07:47,233 --> 00:07:49,133
I got a house in the suburbs.

96
00:07:49,268 --> 00:07:52,897
I've never been there, but I'm
told it's terrific! A pool...

97
00:07:53,039 --> 00:07:56,304
...we can play soccer, you
name it! - Can Bertuccio come?

98
00:07:56,442 --> 00:07:58,842
Do you think so?

99
00:07:59,979 --> 00:08:03,915
I mean, if we invite him,
we get him into our mess, too.

100
00:08:04,050 --> 00:08:06,416
You wouldn't want that.

101
00:09:38,844 --> 00:09:40,675
Take the third left.

102
00:09:40,813 --> 00:09:43,008
- Back to the city?
- Do it!

103
00:09:43,149 --> 00:09:45,640
- We just came that way!
- Me, pilot. You, driver.

104
00:09:45,785 --> 00:09:50,484
- My lion, I want my lion. - Once
mum drove into a gas station.

105
00:09:50,623 --> 00:09:53,421
On the way out, she didn't
know if she had to go...

106
00:09:53,559 --> 00:09:57,586
...right or left. - You're
not in the game, shut up!

107
00:09:57,730 --> 00:10:02,133
- She's as disoriented as a
spinning top. - I want my lion!

108
00:10:02,268 --> 00:10:05,669
- So we get out of here.
- Third left.

109
00:10:15,314 --> 00:10:18,181
- Can I look, dad?
- Yes.

110
00:10:28,961 --> 00:10:30,986
TEG

111
00:10:33,032 --> 00:10:35,762
- Hey, look.
- He won't like it.

112
00:10:35,901 --> 00:10:38,267
- Why not?
- It's hard plastic.

113
00:10:38,404 --> 00:10:40,998
Little Guy's is a cuddly one.

114
00:10:41,507 --> 00:10:43,702
Get the car keys from mum.

115
00:10:43,843 --> 00:10:46,141
Not a word.
Hurry up!

116
00:11:02,862 --> 00:11:06,798
There's a tree behind the house.
Leave it there, no one'll see it.

117
00:11:27,853 --> 00:11:29,616
Come on, Little Guy.

118
00:11:32,858 --> 00:11:35,486
- You know what a call for
action is? - What?

119
00:11:35,628 --> 00:11:39,962
Like in movies when the soldier
warns of an Indian attack?

120
00:11:40,099 --> 00:11:44,695
- Yes. - And the
Indians go: Ooh, ooh, ohh!

121
00:11:45,471 --> 00:11:48,463
If mum or I call for action,
you must do this...

122
00:11:48,607 --> 00:11:51,235
- Drop what you're doing...
- What if...

123
00:11:51,377 --> 00:11:54,676
...we're drinking Nesquik?
... drop what you're doing...

124
00:11:54,814 --> 00:11:58,648
...and come here running,
very, very, very fast.

125
00:11:59,318 --> 00:12:02,185
So, what you do is this.
Listen carefully.

126
00:12:02,321 --> 00:12:03,288
Yes.

127
00:12:03,422 --> 00:12:05,253
- Find this stone...
- Yes.

128
00:12:05,391 --> 00:12:08,986
Stretch out your arms, close
your eyes, lower your head...

129
00:12:09,128 --> 00:12:11,494
...and wriggle through.

130
00:12:12,298 --> 00:12:14,232
- Got it?
- Yes.

131
00:12:14,366 --> 00:12:16,527
- Who wants to try first?
- Me!

132
00:12:17,269 --> 00:12:20,864
Use your arms.
Watch out for your eyes.

133
00:12:21,006 --> 00:12:23,531
When mum or I call
for action...

134
00:12:23,676 --> 00:12:27,407
...find the stone
and wriggle through.

135
00:12:32,852 --> 00:12:35,582
- That way's north. The way
we came. - Yes.

136
00:12:35,721 --> 00:12:40,090
And that's south. It leads
straight to the village.

137
00:12:55,074 --> 00:12:57,372
Be careful!
Don't you fall!

138
00:13:28,641 --> 00:13:31,405
Who lived here before us?

139
00:13:31,744 --> 00:13:33,268
Not a clue.

140
00:13:33,546 --> 00:13:36,379
But somebody lent you
the house.

141
00:13:36,515 --> 00:13:39,416
A friend of a friend
I don't know.

142
00:13:40,186 --> 00:13:42,416
We forgot to bring coal.

143
00:13:42,621 --> 00:13:45,488
Help me gather some
firewood.

144
00:13:50,763 --> 00:13:53,698
HOCUS-POCUS

145
00:15:02,801 --> 00:15:05,326
<i>Harry Houdini
was born in Budapest...</i>

146
00:15:05,471 --> 00:15:10,135
<i>...on March 24, 1874.</i>

147
00:15:10,276 --> 00:15:13,905
<i>He was an escapist,
not a magician, as believed.</i>

148
00:15:14,046 --> 00:15:18,881
<i>An escapist can get out of
the most difficult situations.</i>

149
00:15:28,060 --> 00:15:30,756
- Do you wanna play with me?
- Not even drunk...

150
00:15:30,896 --> 00:15:33,865
...as a skunk!
- I haven't told you what at yet!

151
00:15:33,999 --> 00:15:35,967
Ok, tell me.

152
00:15:39,238 --> 00:15:41,706
<i>You're the skunk, nerd!</i>

153
00:15:44,510 --> 00:15:49,504
<i>To do his job, Houdini had to
be in perfect physical shape.</i>

154
00:15:49,648 --> 00:15:51,775
<i>He ran several miles a day...</i>

155
00:15:51,917 --> 00:15:56,479
<i>...and could stay under water
for four minutes. Four minutes!</i>

156
00:16:01,193 --> 00:16:05,596
<i>Houdini offered rewards to
anyone who could lock him up.</i>

157
00:16:05,764 --> 00:16:09,495
<i>Many accepted the challenge,
only to lose.</i>

158
00:16:09,702 --> 00:16:12,034
<i>He always escaped!</i>

159
00:16:20,312 --> 00:16:23,213
- Yummy!
- Try the chili sauce.

160
00:16:23,349 --> 00:16:26,648
I made the Tabasco too,
but it's a bit hotter.

161
00:16:26,785 --> 00:16:30,312
The amount of firewood I had
to use! It burns quicker than...

162
00:16:30,456 --> 00:16:33,084
Chemical coals burn slower...

163
00:16:33,225 --> 00:16:35,750
What's this?
The rule is...

164
00:16:35,894 --> 00:16:39,125
...science at the table...
... is bad manners!

165
00:16:40,566 --> 00:16:42,932
Can we get to the point?

166
00:16:45,304 --> 00:16:48,296
We'll be staying here for a
while. We don't know...

167
00:16:48,440 --> 00:16:50,067
...for how long yet.

168
00:16:51,844 --> 00:16:54,574
And our stuff?
There's nothing here.

169
00:16:54,713 --> 00:16:56,908
- It's boring!
- It's boring!

170
00:16:57,049 --> 00:17:00,041
I may go by the house
soon and bring some stuff...

171
00:17:00,185 --> 00:17:02,676
...or have someone do it.

172
00:17:04,590 --> 00:17:06,114
No school for a time.

173
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:11,426
I must go to the lab. But dad'll
stay with you for a few days.

174
00:17:11,563 --> 00:17:14,430
- Tell them about the names.
- Just a second.

175
00:17:14,566 --> 00:17:17,364
Be careful around the pool,
it's dangerous.

176
00:17:17,870 --> 00:17:20,998
I'll teach you to use the gas
and fill the tank...

177
00:17:21,140 --> 00:17:23,370
...there's no running water.

178
00:17:23,842 --> 00:17:26,072
Don't answer
or use the phone.

179
00:17:26,211 --> 00:17:28,338
- It's forbidden.
- Why?

180
00:17:28,580 --> 00:17:31,879
If your mum says so,
there's a reason, ok?

181
00:17:33,619 --> 00:17:37,680
Right, from now on,
we change our names.

182
00:17:37,823 --> 00:17:40,917
- Change them?
- No one must know we're here.

183
00:17:41,060 --> 00:17:44,120
If anyone comes asking for us
or phones...

184
00:17:44,263 --> 00:17:46,993
<i>- They're not supposed
to answer! - Wait, wait...</i>

185
00:17:47,132 --> 00:17:49,965
You mean we'll have
other names?

186
00:17:50,102 --> 00:17:51,797
- Yes.
- For ever?

187
00:17:52,805 --> 00:17:54,830
For some time, we said.

188
00:17:55,074 --> 00:17:59,033
Then what if I have a new
name and I phone Bertuccio?

189
00:17:59,178 --> 00:18:01,942
He'll realize it's me,
he's not stupid.

190
00:18:02,081 --> 00:18:04,879
Didn't I make myself clear?
No phone calls, I said.

191
00:18:05,017 --> 00:18:07,952
Not even if your name's
"The Wizard of Oz".

192
00:18:19,665 --> 00:18:22,395
From now on,
we're the Vincents.

193
00:18:22,634 --> 00:18:24,568
I'm David...

194
00:18:24,803 --> 00:18:27,067
...and I'm an architect.

195
00:18:33,479 --> 00:18:36,573
David Vincent,
the architect!

196
00:18:37,216 --> 00:18:40,208
- What? What?
- Like in The Invaders.

197
00:18:40,352 --> 00:18:42,582
Dad is David Vincent!

198
00:18:44,256 --> 00:18:47,054
- Can I choose my name?
- Me too?

199
00:18:47,326 --> 00:18:49,954
Harry.
I wanna be Harry.

200
00:18:53,665 --> 00:18:56,862
Nobody's wearing what we
used to. We could only bring...

201
00:18:57,002 --> 00:19:00,267
...what we had on. Me neither.
- I want MY pajamas.

202
00:19:16,955 --> 00:19:20,254
What's wrong with
this lion that's so hard?

203
00:19:25,230 --> 00:19:27,198
He's softening it up.

204
00:19:58,897 --> 00:20:00,330
What happened?

205
00:20:01,934 --> 00:20:05,131
Did you drink a lot of
coke last night?

206
00:20:06,605 --> 00:20:10,769
- Don't say anything. - Ok, but you
have to promise me something.

207
00:20:10,909 --> 00:20:12,308
What?

208
00:20:12,644 --> 00:20:14,839
You won't drink anything...

209
00:20:14,980 --> 00:20:16,880
...at night, nothing.

210
00:20:17,015 --> 00:20:20,416
No soda water, no water,
coke, nothing.

211
00:20:22,754 --> 00:20:24,312
Is it dead?

212
00:20:25,290 --> 00:20:27,724
It's the one I saw before.

213
00:20:27,859 --> 00:20:29,520
It must have drowned.

214
00:20:29,661 --> 00:20:31,788
It can't drown!
It's a toad!

215
00:20:31,930 --> 00:20:34,057
Toads breathe air.

216
00:20:35,200 --> 00:20:37,691
Obviously, it got trapped.

217
00:20:41,940 --> 00:20:45,307
Yucky creature.
Loot at the skin.

218
00:20:49,781 --> 00:20:54,809
"... Houdini's first stage
name was Eric The Great. "

219
00:20:54,953 --> 00:20:58,650
Because his real name
wasn't Harry, see?

220
00:20:59,358 --> 00:21:01,986
"At first, he was
assisted in his performance...

221
00:21:02,127 --> 00:21:05,358
...by a co-worker from the
factory where he worked. "

222
00:21:05,497 --> 00:21:09,263
Because he was poor and
worked since he was a boy.

223
00:21:09,401 --> 00:21:14,338
"But later, he turned to
his younger brother, Theo. "

224
00:21:16,775 --> 00:21:18,902
Turn it up, little guy.

225
00:21:23,448 --> 00:21:25,916
I wanna watch The Saint!

226
00:21:30,722 --> 00:21:33,452
<i>The Minister denied
categorically that anyone...</i>

227
00:21:33,592 --> 00:21:38,052
<i>...on the list is being held by the
executive power, or in prison...</i>

228
00:21:38,196 --> 00:21:41,597
They gotta whitewash
political prisoners.

229
00:21:41,733 --> 00:21:44,361
- Who, me?
- Let me listen to it.

230
00:21:45,637 --> 00:21:47,298
Tie me up, Little Guy.

231
00:21:47,439 --> 00:21:49,964
- Who, me?
- Yes, you.

232
00:21:55,981 --> 00:21:58,916
<i>We're writing a new chapter
in Argentina's...</i>

233
00:21:59,051 --> 00:22:01,110
<i>...economic history.</i>

234
00:22:01,253 --> 00:22:03,915
Sure, a new chapter.

235
00:22:04,056 --> 00:22:08,083
<i>We'll open our markets
to foreign trade...</i>

236
00:22:08,293 --> 00:22:10,227
Is that okay?

237
00:22:10,829 --> 00:22:12,387
Tighter.

