01:06:42,498 --> 01:06:44,363
And... why don't we stay?

730
01:06:44,500 --> 01:06:46,297
Because we can't.

731
01:06:58,814 --> 01:07:00,304
Look at me.

732
01:07:01,150 --> 01:07:04,347
Hey, look at me.
Look at me now.

733
01:07:06,088 --> 01:07:07,953
Look at me now.

734
01:07:11,260 --> 01:07:12,887
We can't, son.

735
01:07:15,831 --> 01:07:17,355
We can't.

736
01:07:18,267 --> 01:07:19,859
We can't.

737
01:07:23,105 --> 01:07:25,039
Do you understand?

738
01:07:49,065 --> 01:07:52,193
<i>Happy birthday to you.</i>

739
01:07:52,334 --> 01:07:55,599
<i>Happy birthday to you.</i>

740
01:07:55,738 --> 01:07:59,435
<i>Happy birthday, dear Grandpa...</i>

741
01:07:59,875 --> 01:08:02,810
<i>...happy birthday to you.</i>

742
01:08:04,246 --> 01:08:05,543
Blow!

743
01:08:06,282 --> 01:08:07,510
Bravo!

744
01:08:09,385 --> 01:08:11,250
What a lot of smoke!

745
01:08:12,555 --> 01:08:14,819
Move together for a photo.

746
01:08:15,925 --> 01:08:18,086
Cheer up a bit, please.

747
01:08:19,195 --> 01:08:23,632
- Grandpa's teaching me
to drive. - I wanna learn, too.

748
01:08:23,766 --> 01:08:28,066
- Tell grandpa he's nuts.
- He told me you'd say that.

749
01:08:28,204 --> 01:08:31,731
He also told me to tell you
that you learned to drive...

750
01:08:31,874 --> 01:08:34,900
...when you were
younger than me.

751
01:08:35,544 --> 01:08:37,205
That's better.

752
01:08:37,446 --> 01:08:41,849
<i>Sleep, little baby...</i>

753
01:08:42,284 --> 01:08:46,618
<i>...your mommy's in the field.</i>

754
01:08:46,755 --> 01:08:50,452
Leave him, you big boy.
You'll wake him.

755
01:10:54,550 --> 01:10:56,040
May I?

756
01:10:57,953 --> 01:11:00,820
- Look, a shooting star!
- Where?

757
01:11:00,956 --> 01:11:04,915
There. Didn't you see it?
It's gone now. It fell.

758
01:11:05,327 --> 01:11:07,852
When your mom and dad
were engaged...

759
01:11:07,997 --> 01:11:11,398
...we'd sit here after dinner,
looking at the sky.

760
01:11:11,534 --> 01:11:16,369
There were lots of Russian and
US satellites and capsules then.

761
01:11:16,505 --> 01:11:20,236
On a moonless night, you
could see them. We did once.

762
01:11:20,376 --> 01:11:24,244
Mom and her satellite!
It was a shooting star!

763
01:11:24,380 --> 01:11:28,146
- It was a red light!
- No! Red was the wine you had.

764
01:11:29,218 --> 01:11:31,345
What's a shooting star?

765
01:11:31,787 --> 01:11:35,120
If you stare at the sky
without blinking...

766
01:11:35,257 --> 01:11:37,623
...you might see a star...

767
01:11:37,893 --> 01:11:39,622
...come and go...

768
01:11:40,196 --> 01:11:41,788
...at 1000 mph.

769
01:11:42,164 --> 01:11:44,724
- Goodnight all.
- See you tomorrow.

770
01:11:46,702 --> 01:11:50,536
- Come here, grandpa. - No,
you're going to make me fall.

771
01:11:51,540 --> 01:11:53,303
Careful, be careful.

772
01:11:53,442 --> 01:11:54,966
Who's gonna get me up now?

773
01:11:55,110 --> 01:11:58,773
- He will, he's the strongest in
the family. - Stay there, grandpa.

774
01:11:58,914 --> 01:12:02,145
If I get cold, not even a crane
will get me out of here!

775
01:12:02,284 --> 01:12:04,081
They're called
shooting stars...

776
01:12:04,220 --> 01:12:07,121
...but they are really meteorites
or bits of rock...

777
01:12:07,256 --> 01:12:09,383
- No, no science, please!
- Sure?

778
01:12:09,525 --> 01:12:12,119
- Yeah.
- I can't see anything.

779
01:12:12,261 --> 01:12:14,092
You have to be patient.

780
01:12:14,230 --> 01:12:16,721
If you see one,
you can make a wish.

781
01:12:16,866 --> 01:12:20,393
- What have wishes to do with
stars? - Honestly I don't know...

782
01:12:20,536 --> 01:12:24,700
...but they always come true.
I made one once, right here.

783
01:12:26,609 --> 01:12:28,873
- And it came true.
- Really?

784
01:12:29,245 --> 01:12:32,339
Whatever, but
I'm sure it was a satellite.

785
01:12:32,481 --> 01:12:34,642
<i>For God's sake, mom!</i>

786
01:12:35,618 --> 01:12:37,449
<i>- Look, another one!
- Where?</i>

787
01:12:37,586 --> 01:12:39,144
There, look.

788
01:12:39,521 --> 01:12:41,853
<i>You're a liar, mom!</i>

789
01:12:42,892 --> 01:12:45,486
<i>Shooting stars are stones...</i>

790
01:12:45,628 --> 01:12:50,122
<i>...that burn up when they
get close to the atmosphere.</i>

791
01:12:51,200 --> 01:12:53,862
<i>Mom was right about that.</i>

792
01:12:54,603 --> 01:12:55,968
<i>For some reason...</i>

793
01:12:56,105 --> 01:13:01,133
<i>...they are directly
related to wishes.</i>

794
01:13:02,111 --> 01:13:04,545
<i>Dad was right about this.</i>

795
01:13:07,650 --> 01:13:11,017
<i>I watched and watched
till my eyes burnt...</i>

796
01:13:11,153 --> 01:13:13,485
<i>...but I didn't see anything.</i>

797
01:13:14,056 --> 01:13:17,116
<i>That must be why
my wish didn't come true.</i>

798
01:13:35,945 --> 01:13:37,378
Lucas!

799
01:13:39,048 --> 01:13:40,675
Lucas!

800
01:13:45,955 --> 01:13:47,149
Lucas!

801
01:14:06,842 --> 01:14:09,037
You're gonna knock me down.

802
01:14:09,545 --> 01:14:11,479
What happened to the lights?

803
01:14:11,647 --> 01:14:13,274
A local blackout.

804
01:14:15,651 --> 01:14:16,948
What's up?

805
01:14:19,221 --> 01:14:20,745
You got a minute?

806
01:14:22,558 --> 01:14:25,618
Give your mom a hand
before it rains. Come on!

807
01:14:34,403 --> 01:14:36,598
Dead toad!
Dead toad!

808
01:14:43,512 --> 01:14:46,345
This isn't a hole.
It's an elevator.

809
01:14:46,482 --> 01:14:48,950
We'll put it there so
it can go straight...

810
01:14:49,084 --> 01:14:51,052
...to toads' heaven.

811
01:15:05,734 --> 01:15:08,032
I'm gonna wash my hands.

812
01:15:24,953 --> 01:15:26,352
I gotta go.

813
01:15:27,890 --> 01:15:29,790
Now?
You'll get soaking wet!

814
01:15:29,925 --> 01:15:32,450
- Your dad's taking me to
the station. - Can I go?

815
01:15:32,594 --> 01:15:36,121
- No.
- Why not? It's just a second.

816
01:15:36,265 --> 01:15:37,664
It's late.

817
01:15:38,133 --> 01:15:40,363
I waited just to say goodbye.

818
01:15:44,640 --> 01:15:47,507
I'm going, Harry,
this time for good.

819
01:15:48,043 --> 01:15:50,978
- Do you really have to go?
- Yes.

820
01:15:51,380 --> 01:15:52,938
Why?

821
01:15:53,949 --> 01:15:55,814
Wrong question.

822
01:16:03,592 --> 01:16:05,287
Is that it, then?

823
01:16:06,361 --> 01:16:08,556
"Bye", I turn and leave?

824
01:16:10,165 --> 01:16:13,157
- Aren't we friends?
- Friends?

825
01:16:13,735 --> 01:16:17,034
What for? We'll never
see each other again.

826
01:16:22,511 --> 01:16:26,572
- I left my orange T-shirt.
- Go get it yourself.

827
01:17:17,966 --> 01:17:21,732
Lucas! Lucas!

828
01:17:51,166 --> 01:17:53,498
If they ask, say I'm ill.

829
01:17:53,635 --> 01:17:56,763
- Mom's gonna be mad.
- Say you don't know.

830
01:17:56,905 --> 01:18:00,534
Say we went in together
and you didn't see me again.

831
01:18:00,676 --> 01:18:04,077
Okay? Go on,
I'll meet you here.

832
01:18:04,913 --> 01:18:06,710
Oh, I forgot.

833
01:18:09,518 --> 01:18:11,110
Your comic.

834
01:18:18,994 --> 01:18:20,222
<i>Three requirements...</i>

835
01:18:20,362 --> 01:18:24,696
<i>...distinguish the professional
escapist from the amateur.</i>

836
01:18:28,604 --> 01:18:31,505
<i>First, discipline.</i>

837
01:18:33,242 --> 01:18:36,939
<i>The escapist knows
his task is a daily one...</i>

838
01:18:37,079 --> 01:18:39,809
<i>...arduous and restless.</i>

839
01:18:39,948 --> 01:18:42,178
A ticket to Buenos Aires.

840
01:18:43,352 --> 01:18:48,585
<i>Second, concentration. The
escapist must distinguish...</i>

841
01:18:48,724 --> 01:18:52,353
<i>...the important
from the superfluous.</i>

842
01:18:56,932 --> 01:19:00,493
<i>The last requirement
is courage.</i>

843
01:19:04,673 --> 01:19:06,834
<i>The escapist needs it...</i>

844
01:19:06,975 --> 01:19:10,934
<i>...to see his task
through to the end.</i>

845
01:19:12,948 --> 01:19:14,609
Good morning.

846
01:19:18,220 --> 01:19:22,589
- Is Bertuccio in? - No, he's not
back. He's at his aunt's.

847
01:19:22,924 --> 01:19:24,949
That's a pity.

848
01:19:25,193 --> 01:19:29,254
- Tell him I called by.
- Of course, dear.

849
01:19:34,936 --> 01:19:37,336
Can I come by another day?

850
01:19:38,240 --> 01:19:40,367
Yes, but phone first.

851
01:19:45,580 --> 01:19:48,845
<i>The Houdini book tells
a lot of things.</i>

852
01:19:49,284 --> 01:19:52,947
<i>Where he was born,
who his parents where...</i>

853
01:19:53,288 --> 01:19:55,518
<i>...how he became famous...</i>

854
01:19:55,657 --> 01:19:58,751
<i>...what his most difficult
stunts were.</i>

855
01:20:10,772 --> 01:20:13,070
<i>The only thing
it doesn't tell...</i>

856
01:20:13,208 --> 01:20:15,676
<i>...is how he managed
to escape.</i>

857
01:20:19,481 --> 01:20:23,850
He's coming!
Mom, Dad, he's coming!

858
01:20:24,086 --> 01:20:26,520
<i>Mom, Dad, he's here!</i>

859
01:20:26,655 --> 01:20:30,318
<i>Mom, Dad, he's here!</i>

860
01:21:11,066 --> 01:21:13,057
My little boy,
my little boy.

861
01:21:22,744 --> 01:21:25,941
<i>That night we had
a historic match.</i>

862
01:21:46,301 --> 01:21:49,429
Spain to Great Britain with 3.

863
01:21:51,339 --> 01:21:52,636
With 2.

864
01:21:52,774 --> 01:21:55,607
<i>I immediately began
to beat my dad.</i>

865
01:21:55,977 --> 01:21:57,842
<i>I was beating him by far.</i>

866
01:21:58,513 --> 01:22:01,175
Brazil to Sahara with 3.

867
01:22:08,523 --> 01:22:11,981
You move your counters,
I'll move mine, okay?

868
01:22:12,527 --> 01:22:14,290
<i>At the crucial point...</i>

869
01:22:14,429 --> 01:22:17,592
<i>...I controlled
forty-nine countries.</i>

870
01:22:18,366 --> 01:22:21,927
<i>Forty-nine!
And he had only one.</i>

871
01:22:23,305 --> 01:22:25,865
Siberia to Kamchatka with 3.

872
01:22:40,655 --> 01:22:43,954
China to Kamchatka with 3.

873
01:22:58,874 --> 01:23:01,434
Japan to Kamchatka with 3.

874
01:23:02,611 --> 01:23:05,580
Wait!
I'm regrouping!

875
01:23:14,723 --> 01:23:17,248
- May I explain?
- Shut up and play!

876
01:23:22,697 --> 01:23:24,289
Add three.

877
01:23:25,700 --> 01:23:26,928
Pass.

878
01:23:31,673 --> 01:23:34,369
China to Kamchatka with 3.

879
01:23:49,891 --> 01:23:51,950
<i>This went on for hours.</i>

880
01:23:52,127 --> 01:23:54,925
<i>Kamchatka versus
the rest of the world.</i>

881
01:23:55,564 --> 01:23:57,532
<i>But I couldn't beat him.</i>

882
01:23:59,467 --> 01:24:01,662
Kamchatka to Siberia, 3.

883
01:24:50,018 --> 01:24:54,421
<i>The following morning,
Dad called for action.</i>

884
01:24:54,556 --> 01:24:56,114
Hurry up!

885
01:24:59,894 --> 01:25:01,327
Take him!

886
01:26:23,511 --> 01:26:26,708
Mom?
What's wrong with dad?

887
01:27:05,186 --> 01:27:06,881
They also got Oscar.

888
01:27:12,894 --> 01:27:14,589
What do we do now?

889
01:27:33,481 --> 01:27:35,608
Can I go to the toilet?

890
01:27:38,453 --> 01:27:40,546
Wait till dad finishes.

891
01:27:42,757 --> 01:27:45,089
I can go with him,
he's finished.

892
01:28:02,377 --> 01:28:04,402
- There you go.
- Go out.

893
01:28:11,419 --> 01:28:13,444
- Are you there?
- Yes.

894
01:28:13,888 --> 01:28:16,982
Did you see all the people
out there eating?

895
01:28:19,227 --> 01:28:23,095
Do you think they were
also called for action?

896
01:28:29,737 --> 01:28:31,602
Faster! Faster!

897
01:31:33,788 --> 01:31:36,313
PEDRO '75.
HARRY '76.

898
01:32:24,172 --> 01:32:27,664
I need to know they'll
be safe from all this shit.

899
01:32:30,545 --> 01:32:32,604
Do you know what I fear?

900
01:32:35,783 --> 01:32:36,977
No, what?

901
01:32:37,885 --> 01:32:40,445
Never ever seeing them again.

902
01:36:32,086 --> 01:36:35,180
- What would you like?
- Coffee and milk.

903
01:36:39,460 --> 01:36:42,554
Grandma is so happy
about your coming!

904
01:36:45,866 --> 01:36:47,390
And the Little Guy?

905
01:36:48,069 --> 01:36:50,196
He's asleep in the car.

906
01:36:53,574 --> 01:36:56,839
I think that if he wakes and
you're gone, he'll be scared.

907
01:36:56,977 --> 01:36:58,774
He's with mom.

908
01:37:45,659 --> 01:37:47,422
I love you.

909
01:38:01,642 --> 01:38:03,940
I'll wait by the van.

910
01:38:11,352 --> 01:38:12,979
Be a good boy.

911
01:39:04,472 --> 01:39:06,099
I love you very much.

912
01:39:08,876 --> 01:39:10,741
And never forget...

913
01:40:35,396 --> 01:40:37,864
<i>The last time I saw him...</i>

914
01:40:37,998 --> 01:40:40,660
<i>...my dad spoke of Kamchatka.</i>

915
01:40:41,201 --> 01:40:43,328
<i>This time I understood.</i>

916
01:40:44,505 --> 01:40:46,666
<i>Whenever I played...</i>

917
01:40:46,941 --> 01:40:49,102
<i>...dad was with me.</i>

918
01:40:49,677 --> 01:40:51,975
<i>When the game
got tough...</i>

919
01:40:52,513 --> 01:40:55,482
<i>...I stayed with him
and survived.</i>

920
01:40:56,383 --> 01:40:58,214
<i>Because Kamchatka...</i>

921
01:40:58,385 --> 01:41:01,218
<i>...is the place to be
when you want to resist.</i>

922
